00:08:29.780 --> 00:08:34.710
So the subject matter tonight is
in Carolyn's title, "The Oldest

00:08:34.710 --> 00:08:36.980
Question," the oldest and
perhaps one of the most

00:08:36.980 --> 00:08:40.740
profound questions about
the universe we live in,

00:08:40.740 --> 00:08:43.980
which is whether this
extraordinary experiment

00:08:43.980 --> 00:08:46.530
in biology that took
place in this one little

00:08:46.530 --> 00:08:49.960
remote cubby hole, this
little corner of the universe,

00:08:49.960 --> 00:08:52.600
starting four billion
years ago, is unique.

00:08:52.600 --> 00:08:57.310
That's an extraordinarily
profound and simple question.

00:08:57.310 --> 00:08:59.710
The architect and visionary
Buckminster Fuller

00:08:59.710 --> 00:09:03.350
put it very nicely, that
dichotomy, either we are alone

00:09:03.350 --> 00:09:05.070
in the universe or we're not.

00:09:05.070 --> 00:09:07.295
Either way the implications
are staggering.

00:09:09.970 --> 00:09:11.690
And they really are.

00:09:11.690 --> 00:09:14.710
And so what you see is the
end of a long progression

00:09:14.710 --> 00:09:16.610
that is the Copernican
revolution, which

00:09:16.610 --> 00:09:18.160
continues to this day.

00:09:18.160 --> 00:09:20.550
And as we see,
it's a progression

00:09:20.550 --> 00:09:23.010
of ignominy, where
we find ourselves

00:09:23.010 --> 00:09:25.540
to be an exceptional
in our position

00:09:25.540 --> 00:09:29.710
relative to an average star
within an average galaxy in one

00:09:29.710 --> 00:09:31.700
region of the universe
filled with galaxies.

00:09:31.700 --> 00:09:34.520
We also find we're not
even made of the that

00:09:34.520 --> 00:09:37.240
the universe is
overwhelmingly made of.

00:09:37.240 --> 00:09:40.980
And perhaps the final steps
in the Copernican revolution,

00:09:40.980 --> 00:09:44.680
this progression of displacement
of us in importance,

00:09:44.680 --> 00:09:47.520
would be one that I
alluded to in my talk,

00:09:47.520 --> 00:09:49.220
the possibility
of other universes

00:09:49.220 --> 00:09:51.920
beyond our view
and the possibility

00:09:51.920 --> 00:09:55.320
that there are other habited,
inhabited, not just habitable,

00:09:55.320 --> 00:09:58.117
but habited planets
elsewhere in the universe.

00:09:58.117 --> 00:09:59.450
So that's a subject for tonight.

00:09:59.450 --> 00:10:02.670
