The basic story of Mars
is told in this picture

00:26:07.230 --> 00:26:09.460
from the highrise camera,
which is operated out

00:26:09.460 --> 00:26:12.672
of the Lunar and Planetary
Lab, or just down the mall,

00:26:12.672 --> 00:26:14.650
by the University of Arizona.

00:26:14.650 --> 00:26:16.610
It's a dry desert,
for the most part.

00:26:16.610 --> 00:26:18.770
Water cannot exist on
the surface of Mars.

00:26:18.770 --> 00:26:20.900
If you put a cup of
water there right now,

00:26:20.900 --> 00:26:24.970
it would evaporate and boil
away in a fraction of a second.

00:26:24.970 --> 00:26:26.600
So there is no water on Mars.

00:26:26.600 --> 00:26:28.840
But Mars has done more
than tantalize us.

00:26:28.840 --> 00:26:31.120
It's told us that it
is an interesting place

00:26:31.120 --> 00:26:32.320
to look harder.

00:26:32.320 --> 00:26:34.820
And of course, we've done more
than do it with the orbiters.

00:26:34.820 --> 00:26:36.257
We've done it with rovers.

00:26:36.257 --> 00:26:38.840
