01:00:14.350 --> 01:00:15.310
So here's the point.

01:00:15.310 --> 01:00:17.460
We make this prediction
or projection

01:00:17.460 --> 01:00:18.610
based on Moore's Law.

01:00:18.610 --> 01:00:22.430
This is the history of
computers over almost a century.

01:00:22.430 --> 01:00:25.920
And it projects to
a capacity to equal

01:00:25.920 --> 01:00:29.980
our capability in robotic
form in about 20 or 30 years.

01:00:29.980 --> 01:00:31.871
It depends how you
do the projection.

01:00:31.871 --> 01:00:33.370
And, of course,
that could either be

01:00:33.370 --> 01:00:35.700
a computer that
can do what we do

01:00:35.700 --> 01:00:37.700
or a machine that can
generate the ability

01:00:37.700 --> 01:00:40.590
to travel between stars
and colonize the galaxy.

01:00:40.590 --> 01:00:44.290
Both of those possibilities
are projected by our capability

01:00:44.290 --> 01:00:47.500
within a couple of decades.

01:00:47.500 --> 01:00:49.520
And the most important
point is that we don't

01:00:49.520 --> 01:00:52.500
have to go there ourselves.

01:00:52.500 --> 01:00:55.740
We can send the
machines instead of us.

01:00:55.740 --> 01:00:58.340
So a simple model of
tenth light speed travel--

01:00:58.340 --> 01:01:00.090
you're not violating
relativity--

01:01:00.090 --> 01:01:02.390
can have us colonizing
the galaxies.

01:01:02.390 --> 01:01:05.780
And this colonization will
be done by our progeny.

01:01:05.780 --> 01:01:07.270
And our progeny
will be machines.

01:01:07.270 --> 01:01:08.080
They won't be us.

01:01:08.080 --> 01:01:08.840
We're too frail.

01:01:08.840 --> 01:01:10.020
We won't go.

01:01:10.020 --> 01:01:12.720
So let me just talk about
contemplating the aliens

01:01:12.720 --> 01:01:15.110
and what we actually do.

01:01:15.110 --> 01:01:18.150
What's the scientific
experiment to do this?

01:01:18.150 --> 01:01:20.240
The question, the
central question

01:01:20.240 --> 01:01:22.700
in this subject in advance
of finding intelligent life

01:01:22.700 --> 01:01:25.960
elsewhere and with such an
expectation of habitable worlds

01:01:25.960 --> 01:01:27.570
is, where are they?

01:01:27.570 --> 01:01:30.900
And Enrico Fermi asked this
very well posed question back

01:01:30.900 --> 01:01:35.140
in 1950, because he knew that
our civilization is so young.

01:01:35.140 --> 01:01:37.740
And a very small extrapolation
of what we can do

01:01:37.740 --> 01:01:39.510
would have us
traveling the galaxy.

01:01:39.510 --> 01:01:40.710
That's simply the fact.

01:01:40.710 --> 01:01:42.730
No new technologies
are required.

01:01:42.730 --> 01:01:45.660
He also knew that there
were incredibly large number

01:01:45.660 --> 01:01:48.651
of sites for life and
an incredibly long time.

01:01:48.651 --> 01:01:50.400
There could have been
an Earth-like planet

01:01:50.400 --> 01:01:54.220
with an absolute Earth clone,
as close as you could get,

01:01:54.220 --> 01:01:57.840
that formed 6 billion years
before the Earth formed

01:01:57.840 --> 01:02:00.360
and have that much
of a head start on us

01:02:00.360 --> 01:02:01.530
in terms of evolution.

01:02:01.530 --> 01:02:03.210
What would that have spawned?

01:02:03.210 --> 01:02:04.900
There could be
creatures out there

01:02:04.900 --> 01:02:08.690
that are to us as we are
to anaerobic bacteria.

01:02:08.690 --> 01:02:09.840
What would that look like?

01:02:09.840 --> 01:02:12.390
These are the questions
that we expect.

01:02:12.390 --> 01:02:13.580
Nature may have provided.

01:02:13.580 --> 01:02:15.524
And we can't answer
these questions.

01:02:15.524 --> 01:02:17.690
And so the possible answers
to Fermi are, of course,

01:02:17.690 --> 01:02:19.220
diverse, because we
don't know the answer.

01:02:19.220 --> 01:02:20.740
But it's possible
they don't exist

01:02:20.740 --> 01:02:24.280
and we are a unique accident
as a technological, intelligent

01:02:24.280 --> 01:02:25.517
species.

01:02:25.517 --> 01:02:27.850
It's possible they're rare
enough that in time and space

01:02:27.850 --> 01:02:28.660
we're isolated.

01:02:28.660 --> 01:02:30.270
The universe is a big place.

01:02:30.270 --> 01:02:32.040
The galaxy is a big place.

01:02:32.040 --> 01:02:35.320
It's quite possible they're
either unrecognizable or

01:02:35.320 --> 01:02:36.450
inscrutable.

01:02:36.450 --> 01:02:37.650
That we don't they're there.

01:02:37.650 --> 01:02:39.500
We don't know how
to recognize them.

01:02:39.500 --> 01:02:42.470
Their communications, we don't
know how to recognize even

01:02:42.470 --> 01:02:44.400
as communications.

01:02:44.400 --> 01:02:47.580
And another possibility
is that they don't care.

01:02:47.580 --> 01:02:51.790
If we went to a distant
planet and found some lichen

01:02:51.790 --> 01:02:54.360
on the surface of a rock and
wrote it in their tricorder,

01:02:54.360 --> 01:02:56.270
lichen, not very interesting.

01:02:56.270 --> 01:02:58.587
They may be as advanced
to us as we are to lichen.

01:02:58.587 --> 01:03:00.920
And so they've already visited
the Earth and just wrote,

01:03:00.920 --> 01:03:04.030
hm, humans,
uninteresting, move on.

01:03:04.030 --> 01:03:06.920
You know, I mean that's not
the science fiction trope.

01:03:06.920 --> 01:03:08.830
But that's possibly
what happened.

01:03:08.830 --> 01:03:12.270
And then another possibility is
that they actually created us.

01:03:12.270 --> 01:03:15.230
And I'm not going to-- I'm
going to skip ahead a little

01:03:15.230 --> 01:03:17.700
here because I'm getting behind.

01:03:17.700 --> 01:03:20.280
So let me talk about how
we might make contact.

01:03:20.280 --> 01:03:22.860
So this is the scientific
experiment of SETI.

01:03:22.860 --> 01:03:24.990
This is not how it's
going to happen.

01:03:24.990 --> 01:03:29.980
We're not going to tempt them
with groceries or candy or beer

01:03:29.980 --> 01:03:33.230
or anything like that.

01:03:33.230 --> 01:03:37.050
It is possible that
they're among us,

01:03:37.050 --> 01:03:41.960
which I guess logically
also means among you, or me.

01:03:41.960 --> 01:03:44.370
So that's a possibility that
we don't need to look far

01:03:44.370 --> 01:03:46.190
because they're already here.

01:03:46.190 --> 01:03:48.120
But let me just discount
that for a minute

01:03:48.120 --> 01:03:51.440
and say that with what we
know at the moment, the way

01:03:51.440 --> 01:03:54.970
we approach the issue of
technological civilizations

01:03:54.970 --> 01:03:57.140
and communication with
intelligent aliens

01:03:57.140 --> 01:04:00.680
is by looking at the way the
real estate of the Milky Way

01:04:00.680 --> 01:04:03.540
reduces when you ask
that it have planets,

01:04:03.540 --> 01:04:06.870
that the planets be habitable,
that life actually happens

01:04:06.870 --> 01:04:08.600
on those planets
that are habitable,

01:04:08.600 --> 01:04:10.940
that there's sufficient
time, and that the occurrence

01:04:10.940 --> 01:04:13.590
of intelligence that
intelligence gets technology.

01:04:13.590 --> 01:04:16.890
And you can see it's a
diminishing set of terms, which

01:04:16.890 --> 01:04:18.550
turns into the Drake equation.

01:04:18.550 --> 01:04:21.730
And so the Drake equation
is a simple formula

01:04:21.730 --> 01:04:24.280
to calculate the number of
intelligent communicable

01:04:24.280 --> 01:04:26.480
civilizations.

01:04:26.480 --> 01:04:30.500
And what you'll recognize
is that the first three

01:04:30.500 --> 01:04:33.279
terms are astronomical.

01:04:33.279 --> 01:04:34.820
The first three
terms are essentially

01:04:34.820 --> 01:04:37.790
measured by information
I've given you this evening.

01:04:37.790 --> 01:04:41.620
The third, the fourth, fifth,
and sixth and seventh terms

01:04:41.620 --> 01:04:43.100
are indeterminate.

01:04:43.100 --> 01:04:44.430
We have no idea what they are.

01:04:44.430 --> 01:04:46.020
And so you can get
any N you want.

01:04:46.020 --> 01:04:48.780
And that's just the state
we're in at the moment.

01:04:48.780 --> 01:04:49.720
What have we done?

01:04:49.720 --> 01:04:51.510
We've sent little
messages in a bottle.

01:04:51.510 --> 01:04:54.350
This was attached to the
Pioneer 10 spacecraft, now left

01:04:54.350 --> 01:04:55.620
the solar system.

01:04:55.620 --> 01:04:57.970
This was attached to
the Voyager spacecraft,

01:04:57.970 --> 01:04:59.630
now left the solar system.

01:04:59.630 --> 01:05:01.622
And you could critique
it because we don't even

01:05:01.622 --> 01:05:04.080
use that technology on Earth
that we're really showing them

01:05:04.080 --> 01:05:06.660
how clever we are, aren't we.

01:05:06.660 --> 01:05:08.340
Well, OK, I know
there are audiofiles

01:05:08.340 --> 01:05:11.200
that do-- the scientists
involved actually

01:05:11.200 --> 01:05:13.210
defended this because
they said it's actually

01:05:13.210 --> 01:05:15.180
very robust, analog technology.

01:05:15.180 --> 01:05:17.580
We don't know the
longevity of DVDs or CDs.

01:05:17.580 --> 01:05:19.140
There's already
signs they degrade.

01:05:19.140 --> 01:05:23.110
So this will last 100,000
years, not a bad idea.

01:05:23.110 --> 01:05:25.500
So here's the real
state of the experiment.

01:05:25.500 --> 01:05:27.150
If you know anything
about the search

01:05:27.150 --> 01:05:28.800
for extraterrestrial
intelligence,

01:05:28.800 --> 01:05:32.010
mostly using radio signals
and more recently using

01:05:32.010 --> 01:05:35.010
optical pulsed lasers,
you'll know that we've

01:05:35.010 --> 01:05:36.570
had 50 years of silence.

01:05:36.570 --> 01:05:39.954
But the people who do this work
are an indomitable species,

01:05:39.954 --> 01:05:41.370
because they don't
get discouraged

01:05:41.370 --> 01:05:43.030
by 50 years of failure.

01:05:43.030 --> 01:05:45.990
I think I would go away
with my tail between my legs

01:05:45.990 --> 01:05:47.200
after probably a decade.

01:05:47.200 --> 01:05:49.200
But they're some of them
have been plugging away

01:05:49.200 --> 01:05:52.430
for 50 years, like
Frank Drake himself.

01:05:52.430 --> 01:05:55.320
But it's getting interesting
because they are projecting

01:05:55.320 --> 01:06:00.530
that within a decade or so
we will have the capacity

01:06:00.530 --> 01:06:03.820
to listen to our analog
technology of radio

01:06:03.820 --> 01:06:08.840
transmitters or pulse lasers
on any of 100 million stars

01:06:08.840 --> 01:06:11.800
at distances of up
to 3,000 light years.

01:06:11.800 --> 01:06:13.230
That's pretty impressive.

01:06:13.230 --> 01:06:16.200
That means if any
civilization on planets

01:06:16.200 --> 01:06:20.510
around any of 100 million stars
are transmitting information

01:06:20.510 --> 01:06:22.800
by those two methods,
we could detect it.

01:06:22.800 --> 01:06:24.460
And they could detect us.

01:06:24.460 --> 01:06:26.600
And I do think that makes
an interesting scientific

01:06:26.600 --> 01:06:27.100
experiment.

01:06:27.100 --> 01:06:28.849
And they'll just point
out that we've only

01:06:28.849 --> 01:06:32.440
just got into the regime
where we have this capability.

01:06:32.440 --> 01:06:33.590
So it's a transient thing.

01:06:33.590 --> 01:06:36.000
You know, you're only going
detect civilizations that

01:06:36.000 --> 01:06:38.000
are somewhere near your
stage of development,

01:06:38.000 --> 01:06:42.070
because in 50 years we'll
be making baby universes

01:06:42.070 --> 01:06:44.110
and slinging gravity
waves at each other.

01:06:44.110 --> 01:06:45.650
And we'll be doing other things.

01:06:45.650 --> 01:06:48.170
We're not going to be using
lasers and radio transmitters.

01:06:48.170 --> 01:06:50.710
We'll do something else.

01:06:50.710 --> 01:06:53.220
A less comfortable
possibility is

01:06:53.220 --> 01:06:54.990
that there are very advanced.

01:06:54.990 --> 01:06:56.680
And I have mentioned
one possibility

01:06:56.680 --> 01:06:59.560
of them being very advanced
is that they don't care.

01:06:59.560 --> 01:07:04.210
Another one sort of brings
down our sense of ourselves

01:07:04.210 --> 01:07:08.390
because they might view us
a slightly different way.

01:07:08.390 --> 01:07:10.420
And that's sort of the
Stephen Hawking scenario

01:07:10.420 --> 01:07:12.670
where we sort of don't want
to make contact because we

01:07:12.670 --> 01:07:15.280
don't want to know the answer.

01:07:15.280 --> 01:07:18.530
So to conclude, let me give you
the census of habitable worlds.

01:07:18.530 --> 01:07:20.990
Let me give you the full
real estate that's out there.

01:07:20.990 --> 01:07:23.210
And you can do the
math in your head

01:07:23.210 --> 01:07:25.830
of what you think the likelihood
of life on those planets

01:07:25.830 --> 01:07:27.010
is, because we don't know.

01:07:27.010 --> 01:07:29.840
