exoplanets we found.

01:07:43.530 --> 01:07:46.370
That's how many
stars nearby, really

01:07:46.370 --> 01:07:48.350
nearby, within
tens of light years

01:07:48.350 --> 01:07:50.840
we've looked at since 1995.

01:07:50.840 --> 01:07:52.310
These are mostly
the giant planets,

01:07:52.310 --> 01:07:56.170
the terrestrial planets are
motes, too small to see.

01:07:56.170 --> 01:07:57.960
We expect, based
on the numbers I've

01:07:57.960 --> 01:08:01.040
given you in the Kepler results,
a billion habitable worlds

01:08:01.040 --> 01:08:03.200
in the Milky Way galaxy alone.

